\begin{itemize}
  \item Describe the law of conservation of mass and how it applies to chemical
    reactions. \\
    \bf{The \it{Law of Conservation of Mass} states that mass in an isolated
    system is neither created nor destroyed by physical transformations or by
    chemical reactions. The mass of the products in a chemical reaction mush
    equal the mass of the reactants.}
  \item How are single and double replacement reactions different from one
    another? \\
    \bf{A single-replacement reaction replaces one element for another compound.
    A double-replacement reaction exchanges the cations/anions of two ionic
  compounds.}
\end{itemize}

